Below is a **comprehensive list of email templates** your ERP should eventually support, based on the database schema and common school‑management workflows.  
Templates are grouped by module. For each, we give the event, who receives it, what triggers it, and the key dynamic fields.

---

## 📧 Email Template Master List

### 1. Admissions / Inquiries
| # | Template | Recipient | Trigger | Dynamic Fields |
|---|----------|-----------|---------|----------------|
| 1 | Inquiry Confirmation | Inquirer (Parent/Student) | After `inquiries` record created | `inquiry_no`, `student_name`, `parent_name`, `mobile`, `course_name` |
| 2 | Demo Scheduled | Inquirer | `inquiries.demo_scheduled_at` set | `student_name`, `demo_datetime`, `course_name`, `branch_name` |
| 3 | Inquiry Status Change | Inquirer | `inquiries.status` updated | `student_name`, `old_status`, `new_status`, `rejection_reason` (if rejected) |
| 4 | Admission Confirmation | Student + Parent (if `user_id` linked) | After `students` record created with `user_id` | `admission_no`, `student_name`, `batch_name`, `course_name`, `joining_date`, `branch_name` |
| 5 | Student/Parent Account Activation | Student or Parent (when `user_id` is assigned) | After `students.user_id` or `parents.user_id` is set and `auth.users` created | `full_name`, `email`, temporary password (optional), login link |

